name: glutaminyl-peptide cyclotransferase
comment: Involved in the formation of thyrotropin-releasing hormone and other biologically active peptides containing N-terminal pyroglutamyl residues. The enzyme from papaya also acts on glutaminyl-tRNA.

references.title: An enzyme(s) that converts glutaminyl-peptides into pyroglutamyl-peptides. Presence in pituitary, brain, adrenal medulla, and lymphocytes.
Identification of a mammalian glutaminyl cyclase converting glutaminyl into pyroglutamyl peptides.
references.journal: Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A 84:3628-32 (1987) DOI:10.1073/pnas.84.11.3628

references.title: Isolation and properties of glutamine cyclotransferase of dried papaya latex.
